modules.description: Monitors file system events such as file modifications, creations, and deletions by registering watches on directories. It processes events through a polling mechanism and provides access to detailed event data, including file paths and event types. Used to build real-time file synchronization tools or automated build systems.

Provides functions to create and manage inotify descriptors, add and remove file system watches, and read events. Operates on inotify descriptors, file paths, and event selectors to monitor file system changes. Used to track file modifications, directory changes, and other filesystem events in real time.
